// Collab State Management
// Reads, writes, and broadcasts session state for collab sessions.
// Skills use these functions instead of touching the filesystem directly.
// Also tracks snippet mutations (created/updated/deleted) per session.

State is stored as collab-state.json in .collab/sessions/{session}/.
Writes always merge the incoming updates onto the existing state — no fields are silently dropped.
After every write, if a WebSocket handler is provided the new state is broadcast as a session_state_updated message.

---

FUNCTION getStatePath(project, session) -> string
  Returns the absolute file path for the session's collab-state.json.

---

FUNCTION fileExists(path) -> boolean
  Returns true if the file exists, false otherwise.

---

FUNCTION getSessionState(project, session) -> CollabState                   EXPORT
  CALLS: getDisplayName (state-machine)
  Read and parse collab-state.json for the session. Throw if the file does not exist.
  If the state has a state machine ID, compute and attach the human-readable displayName.

---

FUNCTION updateSessionState(project, session, updates, wsHandler?) -> { success }   EXPORT
  CALLS: getDisplayName (state-machine)
  1. Read the existing state from disk (or start with an empty object).
  2. Merge updates onto the existing state field-by-field.
     Updates take precedence; existing values are kept only when the corresponding update is absent.
     lastActivity is always set to the current timestamp.
  3. Ensure the session directory exists, then write the merged state back to disk.
  4. IF wsHandler is provided, broadcast a session_state_updated WebSocket message with the new state.
     Includes all non-null fields and computes displayName if a state machine ID is present.

---

FUNCTION recordSnippetCreated(project, session, snippetId, wsHandler?) -> { success }   EXPORT
  Load the current state, append snippetId to createdSnippets (deduplicated), then save.

---

FUNCTION recordSnippetUpdated(project, session, snippetId, wsHandler?) -> { success }   EXPORT
  Load the current state, append snippetId to updatedSnippets (deduplicated), then save.

---

FUNCTION recordSnippetDeleted(project, session, snippetId, wsHandler?) -> { success }   EXPORT
  Load the current state.
  Add snippetId to deletedSnippets (deduplicated).
  Remove snippetId from createdSnippets and updatedSnippets.
  Save the updated arrays back to state.

---

FUNCTION getSnippetStateSummary(project, session) -> { created, updated, deleted, snippets }   EXPORT
  Load the current state and return counts for each snippet tracking array.
  The snippets field is a deduplicated union of all three arrays.

---

FUNCTION archiveSession(project, session, options?) -> ArchiveResult   EXPORT
  1. Determine archive directory path under docs/designs/{session} (with optional timestamp suffix).
  2. Throw if the session directory does not exist, or if the archive directory already exists.
  3. Create the archive directory.
  4. Copy documents, diagrams, designs, spreadsheets, and snippets from the session into the archive.
     Snippets: skip hidden directories (names starting with ".").
     Documents: note if LESSONS.md was included.
  5. IF deleteSession option is true (default), remove the session directory.
  6. Return the archive path and lists of what was copied.
